ec2.userdata:
<powershell>
mkdir "C:/Program Files/Amazon/Ec2ConfigService/Logs/" -force
$logfile="C:/Program Files/Amazon/Ec2ConfigService/Logs/knife-ec2.log"
# Allow script execution
Set-ExecutionPolicy -ExecutionPolicy RemoteSigned -Force -Scope process
# On windows 2008r2 it will force a reload, which will sever the session
New-ItemProperty hklm:/SOFTWARE/Policies/Microsoft/Windows/System -Name DisableForceUnload -Value 1 -propertytype DWORD
#PS Remoting and & winrm.cmd basic config
$enableArgs=@{Force=$true}
$command=Get-Command Enable-PSRemoting
if($command.Parameters.Keys -contains "skipnetworkprofilecheck"){
    $enableArgs.skipnetworkprofilecheck=$true
}
& winrm.cmd set winrm/config '@{MaxTimeoutms="1800000"}' >> $logfile
& winrm.cmd set winrm/config/winrs '@{MaxShellsPerUser="50"}' >> $logfile
Enable-PSRemoting @enableArgs
#Firewall Config
& netsh advfirewall firewall set rule name="Windows Remote Management (HTTP-In)" profile=public protocol=tcp localport=5985 remoteip=localsubnet new remoteip=any  >> $logfile
</powershell>
